{{Infobox dam | name = Naulong Dam | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | country = Pakistan | location = [[Jhal Magsi]], Balochistan | status = Under-construction | construction_began = July 2012 | opening = June 2015 | cost = PKR 18.082 billion | owner = Government of Balochistan | dam_type = Zoned Earth-fill Dam | dam_height = 186 ft | dam_length = | res_capacity_total = 0.242 MAF | plant_capacity = 4.4 MW }}
'''Naulong Dam''' is an [[embankment dam]] currently under construction on the [[Mula River (Pakistan)|Mula River]], about 30&nbsp;km from [[Gandawah City]] in [[Jhal Magsi]] district of [[Balochistan]], Pakistan. Its Construction Contract has been awarded to Descon Engineering Limited, which is the biggest Contractor in Pakistan.
The zoned earth-filled dam is 186 feet high with a gross storage of 0.242 MAF and a command area of 47,000 acres. It has a hydro power capacity of 4.4 MW.<ref>{{cite web|title=NAULONG DAM PROJECT|url=http://wapda.gov.pk/htmls/naulong.htm|publisher=WAPDA, Govt of Pakistan|accessdate=6 July 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120610193829/http://wapda.gov.pk/htmls/naulong.htm|archivedate=10 June 2012|df=}}</ref>
== History == Feasibility studies for the dam were completed in 2009 and construction for the proposed dam started in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Work at Nai Gaj and Naulong dams to begin|url=http://www.thenews.com.pk/Todays-News-3-114081-Work-at-Nai-Gaj-and-Naulong-dams-to-begin|publisher=The News|accessdate=6 July 2012}}</ref>
